He preceded death wife 60 years, <PERSON>Valerie</PERSON>, parents, sister brother. He survived...
lead_paragraph:
<IMG SRC=/Images/Cobrands/NYTimes/Photos/NYT-0001943718-PERKINSJS_22_006102515.1_191658.jpg lgyOrigName=NYT-0001943718-PERKINSJS_22_006102515.1.jpg ALIGN=LEFT vspace=4 hspace=10>PERKINS--J. Stuart,

86, former President of Volkswagen of America, Inc., passed away on December 25, 2014 in Sarasota, Florida. He was preceded in death by his wife of 60 years, Valerie, also his parents, sister and brother. He is survived by his daughter, Sarah Perkins Cortese, and her husband, John Richard Cortese, both of Sarasota. Stuart Perkins was born in London in 1928 and was one of Volkswagen's first three U. S. employees when the American sales office was established in 1955. In 1964 he was appointed vice president and general manager and became president in 1965. During his tenure as president, he enjoyed great success in expanding Volkswagen's dealership network and increasing sales figures in this country to nearly 600,000 vehicles in 1970. A Celebration of Life Service will take place January 10th 2015 at Church Of The Palms in Sarasota at 2pm. In lieu of flowers donations can be made to SPARCC of Sarasota, All Faiths Food Bank, Church of The Palms or Temple Beth Sholom Preschool Sarasota attn: Vickie Inglese.
headline: {main:Paid Notice: Deaths  PERKINS, J.}
